
        Phax help page.

This command allow you to use phax action in command line.
    Format:

        phax:action [controller] [action] [-p|--parameters[="..."]]


    controller:
        The name of your controller ("help", ...)
        default is "help"


    action:
        The name of the action to call ("test", "ping", ...)
        Will call testAction, pingAction...
        default is "default"


    --parameters:
        Parameters to send to your controller.
        Default is empty array.
        Exemple :

            -p key1:value1 -p key2:value2

        Will send Array([key1] => value1, [key2] => value2)
        You can send multiple parameters.

            -p boolkey

        Will send Array([boolkey] => true)



Examples:

    php app/console phax:action
        =>
            displays this page.


    php app/console phax:action people add -p firstname:tyler -p lastname:durden
        =>
            Call PeopleController::addAction(array $params); with
                firstname and lastname parameters in $params.
            /!\ Important:
                - PeopleController must be declared as service named "phax.people".
                - PeopleController::addAction() must return a PhaxReaction.
                    You can use return $this->get('phax')->reaction(array);
                    in your controller.
                    See PhaxService.
